errer\">How to add a dashboard widget<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/en-us\/docs\/report\/add-a-chart-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">How to add a chart to dashboard<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip <\/span>If you would like to learn more about what is the story behind containers and what drives or the needs for it<\/h3>\n<p class=\"blue\">\u00a0We will know why companies moved from traditional solution architecture to Microservices and how this put containers as the perfect solution for running them, we will get quick intro to clear some definitions, tools and keywords related to this ecosystem, for example.<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\">We will understand what is the different between VM, Container and Hyper-V Container, why we would prefer container over VM and when the VM is better, we will understand the different between container and image and know the life cycle of creating a new image and why I do that, like adding more layers to the base image, push that to container images registry on the cloud, then pull that from the registry to anywhere to have a new container. We will understand also different technologies and services around container, like Docker, Docker Swarm, Kubernetes, Azure Container Services (ACS), Azure Container Registry, etc.- have a look at this post &#8211; have a look at the <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/04\/17\/containers-the-perfect-solution-for-running-microservices\/\"><strong>this post<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"gray\"><span class=\"ion-video\">Video<\/span> You can see <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=qpsMA8On2ok&amp;t=12s\">this video<\/a><\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"gray\">If you would like to find more information about how to debug a Microsoft Dynamics 365 CRM Plugin project. Learn how to put a breakpoint and attach process to the debugger. We will attach w3wp.exe which is the process of IIS. And the second process is microsoft.crm.sandbox.worker process.exe. Create new account on CRM and learn where you can see the activities related with the debugging (next to the summary of your account, in the activities tab).<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Part 1\">\u00a0Dashboards \u2013 Previous Version<\/h3>\n<p>On previous homepage you could only have one <strong>dashboard<\/strong>, you can only have a small section for <strong>new widgets<\/strong> and you couldn\u2019t customize anything else on that page. You couldn&#8217;t remove any of the widgets and you couldn\u2019t lay it out the way your team wanted.<br \/>\nThe image below shows the old team overview page inside <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/08\/license-types-for-visual-studio\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>VSTS<\/strong><\/a>. The image is showing some of the features that you couldn&#8217;t customize in order that dashboard would fit your project&#8217;s needs. You could not remove the top blocks if you do not want them there. If your team didn\u2019t use or burn down the capacity, there was no way to remove them.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/09\/06\/vsts-dashboards\/dashboards-previous-version\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6537\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6537\" title=\"1-VSTS Dashboards - Previous Version\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Dashboards-Previous-Version.jpg\" alt=\"1-VSTS Dashboards - Previous Version\" width=\"763\" height=\"511\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Dashboards-Previous-Version.jpg 820w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Dashboards-Previous-Version-300x201.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Dashboards-Previous-Version-768x514.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><sp